This paper deals with the computational complexity of counting stable matchings, which is a problem in computational social choice. The paper also discusses the reduction of this problem to other well-known problems in computer science, such as counting independent sets in bipartite graphs (#BIS). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
